post_text:
Dear Naperville 203 Families:

On behalf of the Naperville School District 203 administration and Board of Education, I want to take this opportunity to welcome everyone back for the 2020-2021 school year. Tomorrow begins a new chapter in our District’s history and I am excited to see how our community unites to make this year successful. Please take a moment to watch our welcome back video. http://ow.ly/jE9150BdO9s

Thank you for your continued support and commitment to education and to our students. The 2020-2021 theme embodies this collective mission, #203Unites we will unite to return to learn, unite for equity, and together we will unite as a community. Welcome to the 2020-2021 school year!

Dan Bridges
Superintendent

Introducing Ms. Angela Mulligan, Third Grade Teacher

Ms. Mulligan is a familiar face as she was a long term substitute in first grade last year however prior to that had experience as a third grade teacher. She enjoys traveling with her family, reading, and going on walks. This is one of her favorite times of year as she loves all school supplies but especially those that help with organization. The Most Magnificent Thing and A Bad Case of Stripes are two of her favorite picture books. We can't wait to see her in action with her third grade students.

post_text: Today we support our #203businesspartners Naperville Education Foundation . Naperville School District 203 highlights organizations that support our community. Today we support our #203businesspartners Naperville Area Chamber of Commerce . Naperville School District 203 highlights organizations that support our community. Every year the Naperville Area Chamber of Commerce brings community business leaders together for an opportunity to engage with fellow Members, as well as enjoy a casual but FUN golf outing to raise funds for the ongoing efforts of the Chamber in professional development, business connection & advocacy. This year’s theme is The Golden Age of Golf & while golf is the name of the game – we can’t wait to see the vintage golf attire guests are asked to sport! post_text: Naperville School District 203 is proud to announce that Mr. David Sladkey has been selected to receive a Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching (PAEMST). “The PAEMST program, administered by the National Science Foundation (NSF) on behalf of the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy, recognizes outstanding teachers for their contributions to the teaching and learning of science, technology, engineering, mathematics, and/or computer science.” www.paemst.org Mr. David Sladkey has been teaching high school mathematics for 32 years. He has been at Naperville Central High School since 1994 and previously taught at Fenwick High School for six years. David was named Teacher of the Year for Naperville School District 203 in 2007. He currently teaches 9th-10th grade Blended Algebra 1 and Geometry. Follow the link to learn more: https://www.paemst.org/finalist_profile/5072 #Together203

· Support dual language students in grades 6-8 who struggle in reading Spanish and/or English.

post_text: Congratulations to Naperville Central High School, one of 148 schools in the United States that received the SupportMusic Merit Award (SMMA) from The NAMM Foundation! A SMMA Award is an opportunity for an individual school (public, private, parochial or charter) to be acknowledged for its commitment to music education. It is a "school-only" distinction awarded as part of the Best Communities for Music Education program. #together203

post_text: Thank you for the continued support for our students! #together203
shared_text:
Naperville Public Library
April 15 at 2:16 PM ·

To encourage kids to keep reading while school has been disrupted, we delivered 75 book packs to Scott Elementary School today!

Each book pack includes...
1 book (broken down by grade level)
Coloring sheets
Recycled crayons
Activity sheets
Homemade Quarantine Cuisine reading booklets
NPL swag like frisbees or pencils
A special NPL bookmark

Although supplies are limited, these book packs are made for everyone! We're making more to deliver on Monday during lunch pick-up! Thank you to all of our Children's staff involved in creating these book packs, especially Children's Services Associate Tara Barnard! Here is Tara with Principal Hugh Boger at Scott earlier today! #Together203

Thank you for the continued support for our students! #together203

post_text:
Earlier this Spring, the Symphonic Wind Ensemble sent in a recording to be considered by the selection committee for the Illinois SuperState Concert Band Festival hosted by the University of Illinois. The committee then invites only a select few ensembles from across the state of Illinois to participate in the honorary festival. The committee states: “Every ensemble chosen represents the very finest the state has to offer.”

We’re very proud to announce that the Naperville North Symphonic Wind Ensemble was selected for the 2020 Illinois SuperState Concert Band Festival! To be selected to perform is a tremendous honor and we are incredibly proud of our student's dedication and hard work.

Unfortunately, the 2020 festival will not be held this year due to COVID-19; however, this does not diminish the sense of pride and accomplishment that you all can take from this well-deserved accomplishment. Congratulations, NNHS Symphonic Wind Ensemble! #Together203

I sit and watch my son working on his lessons and he has the tools and technology to do so with ease. This makes this current world crisis much easier to deal with. post_text: The Naperville Central FFA chapter, supervised and lead by Mr. Nolan Moss, AG Science, competed at the state veterinary medicine contest on Saturday March 7th and earned 1st place! Varsity members Elizabeth Liu earned 1st place individual, Maggie Martinez earned 3rd place individual, Riley McGrath earned 4th place individual, and Keely Wixted placed 17th high individual out of over 100 competitors across the state. Junior Varsity members included Stella Williams, Claire Chekytis, and Jordan Schrom. Varsity members will go on to compete at the National FFA Convention for the national championship in October. Great work students! #Together203

Maplebrook Home and School Association
February 10 at 11:24 AM ·

Today in 5th grade we are kicking off our space unit!! Students came into the LC wearing NASA all access badges, they went on a Google Expedition to the Moon, they crawled into StarLab and experienced constellations throughout our galaxy, and lastly they worked with AR (Augmented Reality) using a Merge Cube to gain more knowledge about our planets!
Don’t worry...we aren’t leaving the other grades out! Grades 3 and 4 will also get to experience StarLab throughout the week so be sure to ask your child how they liked it!
#WeAreMaplebrook
#Together203

November 23, 2019 at 3:49 PM · Naperville, IL ·

COOPERTITION. A word that combines cooperation and competition. Today, 30 teams representing 14 schools from Naperville School District 203 took part in the inaugural First Lego League tournament supported by the NEF. Elementary school students worked as teams to test their skills at designing, building, coding, and solving problems in order to complete a series of "missions."
